        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 5:48AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 547 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
The Intersection Of Us-380 And Highway 222, or 7 miles east of Irby,
moving northeast at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Throckmorton and Elbert around 605 AM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include The Intersection Of
Us-183 And Us-283, Us-183 Near The Throckmorton-
Baylor County Line, and The Intersection Of Us-380 And Highway 222.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
